<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">The Holy Hand Grenade</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Shen</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Weave/Paradwyn theme deck with one Cald spell. Every card fits into the theme.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Cards</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Quote:</b><I>&quot;And the Lord spake, saying, &#39;First shalt thou take out the Holy Pin. Then, shalt thou count to three, no more, no less. Three shall be the number thou shalt count, and the number of the counting shalt be three. Four shalt thou not count, nor either count thou two, excepting that thou then proceed to three. Five is right out. Once the number three, being the third number, be reached, then lobbest thou thy Holy Hand Grenade of Antioch towards thou foe, who being naughty in my sight, shall snuff it.&#39;&quot;</I> From Monty Python and the Holy Grail.<br />
<br />
<b>Word of warning:</b> It will not be immediately obvious why we chose the Magi and other cards of this deck, but I&#8217;ll explain each card choice in the Strategy section. Every card no matter how far fetched does flow into the theme of this deck. If you ha<!--544-->Ven&#8217;t already figured it out, the theme revolves around the number three and the one Cald spell in the deck. The theme also uses the number se<!--544-->Ven in some places. Remember the number se<!--544-->Ven is a holy number in a lot of Western cultures.<br />
<br />
<b>Disclaimer #1:</b> This deck doesn&#8217;t follow the formula I normally use. If we had done so there would have been aspects of this deck that wouldn&#8217;t have fit into the theme of the deck.<br />
<br />
<br />
Magi:<br />
Taisa<br />
<I>Reason(s) for using as 1st magi:</I> One, his starting energy can be divided by three e<!--544-->Venly. Two, his energize rate and starting energy added together can be divided by three e<!--544-->Venly, thus the first se<!--544-->Ven of the deck is revealed. Three, he starts with all three of his starting cards.<br />
<I>Starting Cards:</I> <!--806-->Speag, <!--808-->Uwamar, <!--812-->Yajo, and two random cards.<br />
<I>Alternate 1st magi:</I> Either M&#8217;Lady <!--817-->Iyori or Ninx. However by changing the magi order you start messing with the theme of the deck.<br />
<br />
M&#8217;Lady <!--817-->Iyori<br />
<I>Reason(s) for using as 2nd magi:</I> One, when she comes out the amount her energy prior to doing anything can be divided by three e<!--544-->Venly. Two, she starts with all three of her starting cards. Three, her power of <b>Natural Selection</b> costs three energy to use.<br />
<I>Starting Cards:</I> Dasia, Weed Hyren, and Crushing <!--423-->Growth<br />
<I>Alternate 2nd magi:</I> Either Taisa or Ninx. Again, by changing the magi order you start messing with the theme of the deck.<br />
<br />
Ninx<br />
<I>Reason(s) for using as 3rd magi:</I> One, her starting energy can be divided by three e<!--544-->Venly. Two, her energize rate can be divided by three e<!--544-->Venly. Three, she starts with all three of her starting cards.<br />
<I>Starting Cards:</I> Blade Hyren, <!--803-->Pagajack, and <!--830-->Weave Mat.<br />
<I>Alternate 3rd magi:</I> Either Taisa or M&#8217;Lady <!--817-->Iyori. Once again, by changing the magi order you start messing with the theme of the deck.<br />
<br />
<br />
There are 21 different cards (minus magi) used to create this deck. Again 21 divided by 3 equals se<!--544-->Ven. This is the second se<!--544-->Ven seen in this deck.<br />
<br />
<br />
Creatures (27):<br />
1 Blade Hyren<br />
3 Dasia<br />
1 Fog Hyren<br />
